o work 10 hours a day, 6 days a week, and sometimes more before a major release??<br><br>Everyone else is sane! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/uarielthemermaid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ariel the Mermaid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess</span><br>  Posts: 1679<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/12/02 4:16:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3308.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.pacbell.net/rpardo/images/mermaid.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Working for Blizzard</span><hr size=1> &quot;Who else besides someone who REALLY loves computer games will be willing to work 10 hours a day, 6 days a week, and sometimes more before a major release&quot;<br><br>Hahahaha. 60 hours a week would have ruled during crunch-mode <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>Hmmm....add around 30-40 hours to that weekly total and you have a better idea of what it takes...<br><br>-Ariel <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/uarielthemermaid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ariel the Mermaid</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/12/02 4:17:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/uxcerebrus.showPublicProfile?language=