uck.<br><br>As long as crunches don't get above 100 hrs over 7 days, it is fairly tolerable.  It does wear down a bit.  Your outside work social life doesn't really do to well though.<br><br>Hopefully, your team leads and managers will keep things structured and organized so crunch time isn't too long.  Crunch is pretty much a fact of life at some point.  Priority queing is just one of those things that seems unavoidably human. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/ukalainatrollbasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalaina Trollbasher</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/empire/alvernaz/icon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/02 12:54:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub114.ezboard.com/flegacyofsteel43089general.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3308.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /shrug</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> hell they sit around in air conditioned offices so much they don't sweat at all!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>haha so true, it has to be to keep all the computers cool. Its SO incredibly cold in the GM pit that in the middle of summer.. folks practically wear full out winter gear <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Kalaina Trollbasher<br><br><i>"I have too much blood in my caffine system."</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#212141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub114.ezboard.com/blegacyofsteel43089.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tuggan>Tuggan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font co